SDK Specification: GiFo-RFC-0128-GAuth-Open-Core-Go-SDK

This SDK implements the GAuth authorization protocol as defined in:
  - GiFo-RFC 0110: GAuth Protocol Engine
  - GiFo-RFC 0111: GAuth Authorization Framework
  - GiFo-RFC 0115: Power-of-Attorney Credential Definition
  - GiFo-RFC 0116: GAuth Interoperability (v2.2)
  - GiFo-RFC 0117: GAuth Policy Enforcement Point (v1.2)
  - GiFo-RFC 0118: GAuth Management API & Administration Interface (v1.1)

================================================================================
EXCLUSIONS — LIMITATIONS ON THE RIGHT TO MAKE DERIVATIVE WORKS
================================================================================

The following features are EXPLICITLY EXCLUDED from this open-source SDK.
They are proprietary to Gimel Foundation / Gimel Technologies GmbH and are
subject to separate license conditions. Users of this SDK MUST NOT — whether
directly or indirectly — integrate:

1. AI-ENABLED GOVERNANCE
   - AI that supports and/or controls the process of an AI deployment lifecycle
   - AI that tracks actions and/or decisions regarding authorization compliance
   - AI that assures the quality of the outcome of AI engagements
   - AI-assisted registration paths (Paths 1-3 as defined in RFC 0118)
   - Risk scoring, regulatory interpretation, compliance reasoning
   - Implied-authority mechanisms

2. WEB3 / BLOCKCHAIN TECHNOLOGY
   - Blockchain technology (including respective Web3 tokens and smart contracts)
     for the extended token of GAuth
   - Any decentralized ledger integration for credential storage or verification

3. DNA-BASED IDENTITIES & POST-QUANTUM CRYPTOGRAPHY (PQC)
   - DNA-based identities or identities based on genetic data
   - AI that tracks the quality of DNA-based identities
   - AI that tracks risks in terms of identity theft or any other risks
   - Post-quantum cryptography (PQC) associated features

4. DECENTRALIZED AUTHORIZATION DELEGATION
   - Delegation of authorization decisions to AI team leads without human oversight

These exclusions are protected by copyright and patent law (patent pending) of
Gimel Foundation. Proprietary implementations are available through separate
licensing from Gimel Foundation or Gimel Technologies GmbH.

For proprietary adapter implementations, see the separate gauth-adapters-gimel
package available under Gimel Terms of Service.

